{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:sirach.35",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 35 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:1",
      "text": "If thou be made the master of a feast, lift not thyself up, but be among them as one of the rest; take diligent care for them, and so sit down.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:2",
      "text": "And when thou hast done all thy office, take thy place, that thou mayest be merry with them, and receive a crown for thy well ordering of the feast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:3",
      "text": "Speak, thou that art the elder, for it becometh thee, but with sound judgement; and hinder not musick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:4",
      "text": "Pour not out words where there is a musician, and shew not forth wisdom out of time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:5",
      "text": "A concert of musick in a banquet of wine is as a signet of carbuncle set in gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:6",
      "text": "As a signet of an emerald set in a work of gold, so is the melody of musick with pleasant wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:7",
      "text": "Speak, young man, if there be need of thee: and yet scarcely when thou art twice asked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:8",
      "text": "Let thy speech be short, comprehending much in few words; be as one that knoweth and yet holdeth his tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:9",
      "text": "If thou be among great men, make not thyself equal with them; and when ancient men are in place, use not many words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:10",
      "text": "Before the thunder goeth lightning; and before a shamefaced man shall go favour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:11",
      "text": "Rise up betimes, and be not the last; but get thee home without delay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:12",
      "text": "There take thy pastime, and do what thou wilt: but sin not by proud speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:13",
      "text": "And for these things bless him that made thee, and hath replenished thee with his good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:14",
      "text": "Whoso feareth the Lord will receive his discipline; and they that seek him early shall find favour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:15",
      "text": "He that seeketh the law shall be filled therewith: but the hypocrite will be offended thereat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:16",
      "text": "They that fear the Lord shall find judgement, and shall kindle justice as a light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:17",
      "text": "A sinful man will not be reproved, but findeth an excuse according to his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:18",
      "text": "A man of counsel will be considerate; but a strange and proud man is not daunted with fear, even when of himself he hath done without counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:19",
      "text": "Do nothing without advice; and when thou hast once done, repent not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:20",
      "text": "Go not in a way wherein thou mayest fall, and stumble not among the stones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:21",
      "text": "Be not confident in a plain way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:22",
      "text": "And beware of thine own children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:23",
      "text": "In every good work trust thy own soul; for this is the keeping of the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.35.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 35:24",
      "text": "He that believeth in the Lord taketh heed to the commandment; and he that trusteth in him shall fare never the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
